27/04/2005
STRASBOURG, France -- Serbia-Montenegro President Svetozar Marovic told the Parliamentary Assembly of the Council of Europe in Strasbourg Tuesday (26 April) that the federal union views Europe as its choice, goal and future. Marovic also vowed that in pursuing this long-term objective, Belgrade would continue co-operating fully with international institutions, particularly the UN war crimes tribunal. As for Kosovo's future status, the president stressed that the province has only one choice: to be multiethnic, European, and safe for all its residents. (CoE Web site, Beta, B92 - 26/04/05) 
